        "content": "<p>Hi guys, I want to prove</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">∏</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∏</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∏</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>where <code>s</code> is a finset and both<code>f x</code>&amp; <code>g x</code> are nonzero natural number through out <code>s</code>. I discovered a thing called <code>Finset.prod_div_distrib</code> in mathlib but it asks me to fill in a DivisionCommMonoid, what can I do to resolve this?</p>",
